unenigmail

Unenigmail strips Enigmails PGP encryption from emails within a supplied mbox file.
Note: This is only recommended if you store your emails in a secure environment. For example an mbox on your local disk with disk encrypion.

Usage:
  -h                            this screen
  -f <file name/folder name>    file or folder with files to strip

  
Example (single File):
  unenigmail -f "/home/me/.thunderbird/.default/Mail/Local Folders/Inbox.sbd/friends"
Example (folder):
  unenigmail -f "/home/me/.thunderbird/.default/Mail/Local Folders/"

  
Compilation dependencies:
  lazarus
Compilation:
  lazbuild --build-mode=Release unenigmail.lpi
